2	 * nsg signal — operator-facing event emission.
3	 *
4	 * The patron-facing counterpart to the anima-only `signal` tool exposed
5	 * by the Clockworks. Both surfaces run the exact same three layers of
6	 * validation against the proposed event name; this command duplicates
7	 * the validator inline rather than importing the Clockworks plugin so
8	 * the CLI keeps its zero-dependency-on-plugin-packages discipline (see
9	 * `start.ts` for the same pattern with Spider/Oculus apparatuses).
10	 *
11	 * Why hand-written instead of going through the auto-builder?
12	 *
13	 *   - The Commander auto-builder cannot JSON-parse a `--payload <json>`
14	 *     flag — that parsing happens here, locally, before the call into
15	 *     `ClockworksApi.emit`.
16	 *   - The auto-builder's positional convention only promotes `id`/`*Id`
17	 *     params; this command needs `<name>` as a positional argument.
18	 *   - The emitter must default to `'operator'` (commission decision D4),
19	 *     not the `'anima'` default the tool uses.
20	 *
21	 * The anima-facing `signal` tool in
22	 * `packages/plugins/clockworks/src/tools/signal.ts` is marked
23	 * `callableBy: ['anima']` so the CLI auto-builder skips it — there is
24	 * no auto-registered duplicate of this command (commission decision D6).
25	 *
26	 * See commission c-modhilaw decisions D2, D4, D6, D7, D11.
27	 */
28	
29	import { Command } from 'commander';
